snippet: Both sides achieve some concessions in the new musicians’ contract at the New York Philharmonic.
abstract: Contract agreement New York Philharmonic reaches with its musicians will keep music playing at Avery Fisher Hall and spare city from bitter labor unrest that has set off damaging strikes and lockouts at orchestras nationwide; both sides achieved some concessions in deal.
lead_paragraph: Both sides achieve some concessions in the new musicians’ contract at the New York Philharmonic.

headline.main: Deal Gives Philharmonic Musicians Modest Gains
headline.print_headline: Deal Gives Philharmonic Musicians Modest Gains
